## What We're Building

Saber is an AI-powered diagnostic tool that helps teachers understand *why* their English Language Learner (ELL) students are struggling — not just *that* they are. When a student fails a standardized test, Saber re-tests them in Spanish and uses AI to determine whether they missed the question because they didn't understand the material, or because they couldn't understand the English wording of the question.

That distinction changes everything about how a teacher responds.

---

## The Problem

Georgia tests all 108,752 ELL students exclusively in English. When those students fail, teachers have no way to tell whether it's a language problem or a knowledge problem — so most get routed into the same remediation regardless. About 50% of ELL special education referrals may be language-based misidentifications. Each incorrectly placed student costs $13,000–$17,000 per year in unnecessary services. No existing commercial tool uses AI to make this distinction automatically.

---

## How It Works

1. A teacher uploads a CSV of standardized test scores
2. Saber identifies which questions each student missed
3. AI (Gemini) generates a Spanish-language equivalent of each missed question
4. The student retakes those questions in Spanish — typing or speaking into a mic
5. AI compares the student's English and Spanish responses and classifies each gap
6. The teacher sees a color-coded dashboard with an AI explanation per student
7. The student gets a personalized quest line targeting their specific gap type

---

## Gap Types

| Classification | What It Means | What Saber Does |
|----------------|---------------|-----------------|
| `LANGUAGE_GAP` | Student knew the content — the English wording blocked them | Routes to English vocabulary and academic language exercises |
| `CONTENT_GAP` | Student genuinely doesn't understand the subject matter | Routes to targeted subject instruction quests |
| `MIXED` | Both language and content issues are present | Routes to a combined learning path |

